From 0000000000000000000000000000000000000000 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: pai-nix <pai-nix@localhost>
Date: Sun, 3 May 2026 14:00:00 +0200
Subject: [PATCH 6/6] Fix Pulse case-sensitive path construction on Linux

PAI v5.0.0 ships its Pulse subsystem with inconsistent directory casing.
The on-disk directory is "PULSE" (all caps — verified by extracting the
upstream tarball and listing Releases/v5.0.0/.claude/PAI/), but 15 path-
construction sites across 11 live source files spell it as "Pulse"
(mixed case).

On macOS (case-insensitive HFS+/APFS by default) every "Pulse" path
resolves to the same directory as "PULSE" — bug invisible upstream.
On NixOS / Linux ext4 (case-sensitive) every join(...,"Pulse",...)
produces a path that does not exist; reads fail with ENOENT and writes
either get silently dropped or land in a parallel ghost directory at
~/.claude/PAI/Pulse/ depending on parent-dir creation logic.

User-visible symptoms on NixOS:

  1. Observability dashboard returns 404 for every page (/, /agents,
     /work, /telos, /health, /algorithm, /security). The static Next.js
     export at PAI/PULSE/Observability/out/ is correct and complete,
     but observability.ts looks for it under PAI/Pulse/Observability/out/.

  2. All four Pulse cron jobs (assistant-tasks, cost-aggregation,
     healthcheck, airgradient-poll) report "result":"error" in
     /healthz. run-job.ts spawns each job with cwd set to
     PAI/Pulse/ — non-existent on Linux — and dies before the job
     script runs.

  3. iMessage / user-index / notification-governor / DA scheduler /
     github-work / cost-aggregator state never persists across
     restarts. Each module writes to its own ghost path under
     PAI/Pulse/state/* which on a case-sensitive FS is a directory
     that nothing else reads from.

Fix scope: replace every '"Pulse"' string literal with '"PULSE"' in
path-construction contexts. The change is platform-agnostic — "PULSE"
matches the canonical on-disk name and works on both case-sensitive
and case-insensitive filesystems. macOS users see no behavior change
(both forms resolved to the same directory there before).

